          "Raised in Teran after the fall of the Shah. You were brought in to the faith at a young age and it was all you knew. The connection to Allah grew deeper as you felt your soul in harmony with the sounds of creation. Your avatar awoke shortly after your 16th birthday and were quickly pulled in to the Ahl-i-Batin and trained in the ways of being a mage. You understood the secret ways that Mohamed took and hid in the Kaaba and learned to use those ways to make Allah’s presence known upon the world. Being a woman you were able to hide from most of the encroachment of the technocracy in the hunt for the black blood of the soil, but you were not able to hide from the pale souls that tracked your movements and manipulations. One day on a trip to Qatar you drank from a glass of tea that was drugged by cell of Banu Haquim that had been tracking you. You awoke to feel your avatar taken back by Allah and the new half life of a Ashirra member foist upon you. You sent a missive to your old teacher and explained what had occurred. He offered to kill those that changed you but with some time you both came to an understanding that not all mysteries under heaven can be solved and that you would maintain your friendship as long as Allah allowed. He did send you a final gift of a blessing to let you see the spirit world and communicate with wraiths. Your training under the Banu Haquim was hard but your passion to learn from those who had lived for centuries drove you to keep trying harder. With your modern knowledges you were asked by your cell to leave Amalut and support the Banu Haquim in the courts of the Ashirra. In the sect of the chosen you were in your element, learning when to be quiet and when to respond like the judges both your blood and your soul belonged to. Then the rising of Ur-Shulgi the Burnt Soul, broke the Clan. The Web started hunting their brothers for their blood and the Ashirra looked west for the first time for aid, You were part of the diplomatic core quietly attending the meetings while your Vizier brothers negotiated a pact with the unfaithful. But we would not forget the crimes of the past so easily. Forever we remember the curse and the demon blessed words of Ulgon Bey will not bring back the brothers him and his servants killed for centuries. As an eye for an eye, they had opened Amalut, we would open Vienna Chantry. As an expert at hiding in plain sight you were tasked to walk in to the Vatican with the hand of god burning your every step to place on the altar of St. Peter's Basilica the documents to doom the Tremere Pyramid to the ashes of history, For a Judge does not allow a crime to go unpunished. In leaving that mission, the Odense Pact was signed before the missiles flew to Austria. Your cell gave you’re their blessing and asked you to leave the Ashirra and Europe to the Americas, where there were many opportunities to support and lead the judges of Caine to glory."
        ],
        [
